# SHOCK / BOUNDARY - LAYER INTERACTION AT 10 DEGREE DEFLECTION ANGLE
#
# Reference:
#   "Documentation of Two-Dimensional Impinging Shock/Turbulent Boundary Layer Interaction Flow"
#   Schulein, E. & Krogmann, P. & Stanewsky, E.
#   DLR Report DLR IB 223-96 A 49
#   October 1996
#
# Shock generator: 
#   x_gen =  23.0 mm
#   y gen = 115.0 mm
#
# Separation:
#  'S' = 334 ± 1 mm   Section #101
#  'R' = 345 ± 1 mm   Section #102
#
# Variables:
#   SecNo    = measurement section number
#   x        = axial    coordinate
#   z        = spanwise coordinate
#   Me       = Mach number at edge of boundary layer
#   Pwall    = pressure at wall
#   delta    = boundary layer thickness where U/Uedge=0.995
#   deltas   = boundary layer displacement thickness
#   theta    = boundary layer momentum     thickness
#   Cf       = skin friction coefficient
#   H        = shape factor, H=delta*/theta
#   deltasin = transformed "incompressible" displacement thickness
#   thetain  = transformed "incompressible" momentum     thickness
#   Hin      = transformed "incompressible" shape factor
#   n        = exponent in power law, U/Udelta=(y/delta)**(1/n)
#   Pi       = Cole's law of the wake parameter
#   Mtau     = friction Mach number, Mtau=utau/awall
#   betaq    = wall heat transfer parameter, betaq=qwall/(rhowall*Twall*utau*Cp)
#
Variables="SecNo","x(mm)","z(mm)","Me","Pwall(Pa)","delta(mm)","deltas(mm)","theta(mm)","Cf","H","deltasin(mm)","thetain(mm)","Hin","n","Pi","Mtau","betaq"
Zone T="Schulein, et al. (1996)", F="POINT"
#Sec   x   z    Me Pwall delta deltas theta       Cf    H deltasin thetain   Hin     n    Pi  Mtau  betaq
#No.  mm  mm          Pa    mm     mm    mm                     mm      mm
